org.apache.freemarker.core.util

Class StringToIndexMap

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.freemarker.core.util.StringToIndexMap

  • public final class StringToIndexMap
extends Object
    Maps string keys to non-negative int-s. This isn't a Map, but a more specialized class. It's immutable. It's slower to create than HashMap, but usually is a bit faster to read, and when HashMap gets unlucky with clashing hash keys, then it can be significantly faster.

    Instances of this class are immutable, thread-safe objects.
